# Goals

## AutoDown-G1 Block-Based Markdown Editor
**Status:** implemented
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** UiSystem-G1

- [x] Tiptap/ProseMirror-based editor with Markdown round-trip serialization
- [x] Support headings (H1–H3), paragraphs, lists (bullet/ordered/task), blockquotes, code blocks, horizontal rules
- [x] Inline formatting: bold, italic, strikethrough, links, inline code
- [x] Image embedding with base64 support
- [x] Slash menu (`/`) for quick block insertion
- [x] Bubble menu for inline text formatting
- [x] Drag handle for block reordering

## AutoDown-G2 Table Editor with Resizable Columns and Rows
**Status:** implemented
**Tags:** stack:frontend
**Depends on:** AutoDown-G1

- [x] Table insertion via slash menu (`/table`)
- [x] Table structure editing: add/delete rows and columns, merge/split cells
- [x] Column width resizing via draggable handles
- [x] Row height resizing via draggable handles
- [x] Double-click on column boundary resets column width to auto
- [x] Double-click on row boundary resets row height to auto
- [x] Column widths and row heights persist through Markdown serialization via IAL
- [x] IAL syntax: `{cols:[120,"auto",200], rows:[40,"auto","auto"]}`
